DTSTAMP:20260420T040722
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T220000
SUMMARY:Fundraising concert 15$ in solidarity with land defenders
LOCATION:1900 Le Ber (métro Charlevoix)
DESCRIPTION:2026-05-02 20:00:00\n\n1900 Le Ber (métro Charlevoix)\n\nhttp
 s://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6074430797\n\nFundraising concert in solida
 rity with land defenders (km 134)\nwith UZU\, 狗日的\, TENAZ &amp\; HUR
 TA\nAt: B7\, Tiohtià:ke (Montreal)\nDoors: 8PM\nConcert: 9PM\nAdditional 
 infos: All funds will be donated to the km 134 blockade\nThanks for your s
 upport\, generosity &amp\; solidarity!\nCamp Souveraineté\, at km 134 on 
 the Parent Road\, is located on the unceded ancestral territory belonging 
 to hereditary chiefs Robert Echaquan and Jean-Paul Echaquan. The site is a
  space for monitoring and protecting protected areas and for defending anc
 estral rights\, which necessarily requires consultation with hereditary ch
 iefs before any form of resource extraction.\nIn addition to maintaining c
 ontinuous monitoring against illegal logging\, the land defenders are buil
 ding facilities to welcome Atikamekw people living in nearby towns who wis
 h to reconnect with their roots.\nSome have left their communities to work
  in municipalities and now have limited access to ancestral Nehirowisiw As
 ki knowledge.\nThis place of transmission is open to all who wish to recon
 nect with their language and identity.\nSaturday\, May 02\, 08:00 PM-11:55
  PM\nin 1 month\nBatiment 7 / Tapage\n1900 le Ber\n&nbsp\;\n&nbsp\;
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6074430797
END:VEVENT
